race.comment: SAINT BOOM (11) was narrowly defeated in the same maiden at Morphettville last time. She has been placed in four of her 10 starts and looks set to improve second-up to 1400m. Gets the blinkers on now for Holder and suspecting drawing away from the fence is a big tick. Can shed the maiden tag this time. I AM RALPH (3) is another that looks an each-way chance off his recent form. He was well held in his only two runs at 1400m but might be ready now. ALPINE LEE (13) can atone after being beaten as favourite last start, while THAVMA (8) might be an improver at a big price after things didn't go right at all last time.
